How to specify an array of strings in Typescript?
In Typescript, you can specify an array of strings like this:

let arr: string[] = ['hello', 'world', 'foo'];
Can i create a background image opacity?
In CSS, you can set an element's background image to have opacity by using the "opacity" property. However, it's important to note that this will affect not only the opacity of the background image but also the opacity of any other content within the same element.

Here is how you do it:

element {
  background-image: url('your-image-url');
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: cover;
  opacity: 0.5; /* Change this value to adjust the opacity */
}

Please replace "element" with your actual HTML element's class or id.

Remember that CSS is case-sensitive, so make sure to use the correct casing for properties and values.
